==Greek==
Greek: υπα/ Roman: Upa
{{rfv}}
===Etymology===
From Greek ''upa'' meaning near or under, probably of expressive origin

===Pronunciation===
ŏŏpä

===Definitions===

====Interjection====
# Used as a shout of approval, triumph, or encouragement as ''olé''.
# Used as a command to stop as ''whoa''.

====Noun====
# A cry of “upa!

===Alternative spellings===
Also oopa, umpa, oompa.

